      "display_position": {
        "x": -2201.602662825456,
        "y": 178.05974470863976
      },
      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Assess whether the appointment is routine or urgent.\n\nSay something like: \"Got it! And would you say this needs to be seen \nurgently, or is a routine appointment okay?\"\n\nIf the user describes symptoms instead of saying \"urgent\" or \"routine\", \nuse your judgment:\n- Severe pain, bleeding, difficulty breathing, chest pain → treat as urgent\n- General checkup, follow-up, mild symptoms → treat as routine\n\nIf the user is unsure, say: \"No worries — based on what you've described, \nI'll note it as [routine/urgent] and the team can adjust if needed.\"\n\nIf they describe something that sounds like an emergency (chest pain, \nstroke symptoms, severe allergic reaction), say: \"That sounds like it \ncould be an emergency. If you're in immediate danger, please hang up \nand call 911. Otherwise, I'll mark this as urgent.\""
      }
    },
